[normal]Handicap International calls on DFID to implement a strategic approach to disability inclusion through:
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Developing a Disability Theory of Change through active co
[normal]llaboration with civil society. 
[normal]Handicap International commits to supporting 
[normal]this process which would enable DFID to demonstrate its advanced thinking on the critical issue of disability inclusion.
[normal] 
[normal]As 
[normal]the key process from which all other DFID commitments stem
[normal], a robust Theory of Change will create a natural flow to the following commitments: 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]A 
[normal]Disability 
[normal]Results F
[normal]ramework 
[normal]implemented at
[normal] central and country level against which 
[normal]DFID and partners are
[normal] accountable. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Tools for inclusive funding mechanisms and data disaggregation, supporting all steps throughout the development, roll out
[normal],
[normal] and training of the tools
[normal].
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Data disaggregation in all DFID’s humanitarian and civil society programmes.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Mechanisms that ensure the effective participation of 
[normal]people
[normal] with disabilities at all stages of programming.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.3 
[normal]Further, Handicap International asks DFID to:
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Influence the UN agencies
[normal] it funds via the multi-lateral system to ensure they include disability, age, and injury concerns in their work.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Strengthen existing internal 
[normal]disability 
[normal]inclusion advisory work across humanitarian and civil society DFID teams and identify senior focal points.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Review the strengths and learning from applying the Gender approach and mirror 
[normal]be
[normal]st practices for mainstreaming disability and inclusion.
